[4] UK (Surrey & Sussex)
Date: Thu 22 Sep 2011
Source: Eagle radio Nres [abbreviated & edited]
http://www.964eagle.co.uk/news/local-news/515635/mmr-warning-as-measles-cases-increase/


We are being urged to get the MMR jab for our children following an
outbreak of measles in Surrey. New figures show there were 115 cases
in Surrey and Sussex in the 1st 6 months of this year [2011]. That's
more than double the number for the whole of last year.

Dr Angela Iversen is from the Surrey and Sussex Health Protection Unit
and says the virus is spreading through un-vaccinated children: "Quite
a lot of that was linked to foreign travel to Europe where there are
some very large outbreaks of measles going on, particularly in France.
We know that the figures went down somewhat during the summer
holidays, but I am afraid that we have started to see some early signs
that we are getting a small number of cases back.

