[10] New Zealand (Canterbury)
Date: Tue 20 Sep 2011
Source: NZCity [edited]
http://home.nzcity.co.nz/news/article.aspx?id=136738&cat=1005&fm=newsmain,narts


A female Canterbury University student has been diagnosed with the
disease [measles] after travelling to Auckland recently. Almost 150
cases have already been confirmed in Auckland. Canterbury medical
officer of Health Dr Ramon Pink says there may be a link with Rugby
World Cup 2011 travel. "With the accelerated number of cases over the
last couple of days in Auckland, I think that there is increased risk
of seeing more measles cases down in the south and in the Christchurch
area," he says.

Dr Pink says the key to preventing an outbreak in the south is for
people to look out for early signs: a fever, runny nose and
conjunctivitis.

