[11] NZ (Air travel alert)
Date: Fri 23 Sep 2011
Source: NewstalkZB [edited]
http://www.newstalkzb.co.nz/newsdetail1.asp?storyid=205340


Health officials battling to contain an outbreak of measles have found
infected people have travelled on another 2 domestic flights. They
were Air New Zealand afternoon flights that left Auckland for
Wellington at 12.30 pm on Friday 9 Sep 2011 and a 2:30 pm flight from
Wellington to Auckland last Saturday 24 Sep 2011. Passengers on those
flights are being urged to immediately check their immune status and
that of their children.

It's already been revealed infected people have in the past 3 weeks
travelled on 4 flights between Auckland and Wellington, and one
between Christchurch and Auckland.

There have been a total of 167 confirmed cases of measles in the
Auckland region in the past 6 months, 24 of which required
hospitalisation. 27 people are in quarantine.

[Byline: Lesley Deverall]

